  <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide uppercase mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a conveyor reject system?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>A conveyor reject system removes non-conforming product from the line after a metal detector, checkweigher, vision system, or X-ray scanner detects a defect. The mechanism activates within 20–500ms and diverts the defective product into a locked reject bin while good product continues downstream.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What types of reject mechanisms exist?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Four main types: <strong class="text-ink">Air blast</strong> (compressed air, fastest, lightweight products). <strong class="text-ink">Pusher arm</strong> (pneumatic/servo cylinder, 50g–25kg). <strong class="text-ink">Diverter gate</strong> (pivoting sweep arm, medium-heavy products). <strong class="text-ink">Drop-out belt</strong> (belt retracts, no product contact, any weight). Choose based on product weight, line speed, and whether the product tolerates lateral contact.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How fast must a reject system respond?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>The mechanism must complete its cycle within the product transit time from detector to reject point. At 200 FPM with 12 inches of distance, transit time is 300ms. Air blast: 20–50ms. Pusher arm: 50–150ms. Diverter gate: 100–300ms. Drop-out belt: 150–500ms. Higher conveyor speeds require faster mechanisms and shorter detector-to-reject distances.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            Do I need a reject confirmation sensor?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Yes, for regulated industries (food, pharmaceutical) and critical quality defects (metal contamination). The confirm sensor verifies the product entered the reject bin. Failed confirmation triggers an alarm and optionally stops the line. Major retailers and food safety standards (BRC, SQF) increasingly mandate reject confirmation on metal detector and X-ray systems.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

